16 "20-1-12.
17 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
18 (1) 'Organ' means a human organ, including the eye, that is capable of being transferred
19 from the body of a person to the body of another person.
20 (2) 'Public school employee' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section
21 20-2-910.
22 (3) 'Public school teacher' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section
23 20-2-880.
24 (4) 'Postsecondary employee' shall include any person employed not less than half time
25 by the University System of Georgia or any institution thereof or the Technical College
26 System of Georgia or any unit thereof; provided, however, that such term shall not be
27 deemed to include any emergency or temporary employee.
28 (b) Each public school teacher and public school employee shall be entitled to receive the
29 following leaves of absence, without loss of pay:
30 (1) Not more than seven days for the purpose of bone marrow donation for
31 transplantation, which shall not be charged against or deducted from any annual or sick
32 leave and shall be included as service in computing any retirement or pension benefits;
33 and
34 (2) Not more than 30 days for the purpose of organ donation for transplantation, which
35 shall not be charged against or deducted from any annual or sick leave and shall be
36 included as service in computing any retirement or pension benefits.
37 (c) Each postsecondary employee shall be entitled to receive the following leaves of
38 absence, without loss of pay:
39 (1) Not more than seven days for the purpose of bone marrow donation for
40 transplantation, which shall not be charged against or deducted from any annual or sick
41 leave; and
